Hardwood made a huge mistake this past update removing the Cut Deck option 
from games. The deals without cutdeck are so one-sided it isn't even worth 
playing anymore. I guess you should expect that with internet cards. On top 
of this, they charge too much for their dying app. They clearly haven't 
learned from their drastic decline in users that being a money pit card 
game doesn't sit well with fans. I will be moving on to any of the several 
other spades options out there.
replyContent:
We're trying to simplify the interface a bit.   The Cut the deck options in practice just rotates what seat gets what hand.  Which was already random, so it was more just a psychological tool than one that actually impacts the deal...and always was.  

The best defense against the luck of bad cards is to play games where things even out a bit.
